    <!--
        ================================================================================
        BUILD STRATEGY: IDE-Friendly Default + Profile-Based Logback Testing
        ================================================================================

        This project uses a two-tier testing strategy to provide an optimal development
        experience in IDEs while maintaining comprehensive test coverage in CI/CD.

        THE CHALLENGE:
        ==============
        - Core tests (Meter, Watcher, Reporter) require slf4j-test-mock (MockLogger)
        - Logback integration tests require logback-classic (real Logback Logger)
        - SLF4J ServiceLoader can only bind ONE implementation at runtime
        - Having both on classpath causes runtime ClassCastException
        - IDEs (especially IntelliJ) struggle with dual build configurations

        THE SOLUTION:
        =============

        1Ô∏è‚É£  DEFAULT BUILD - IDE-Friendly (No Profile Needed)
        ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
        What:    Standard Maven build or IDE import
        Tests:   Meter, Watcher, Reporter + support classes (~1441 tests)
        Runtime: slf4j-test-mock (MockLogger)
        Exclude: logback-classic dependency
        Exclude: **/logback/**/*Test.java test classes
        Exclude: src/logback-main/java source directory
        Exclude: src/logback-test/java test directory

        IDE Support: ‚úÖ Full support (run, debug, code coverage, refactoring)

        Command: mvn clean test                      # or just run tests in IDE
        Result:  1441 tests pass

        2Ô∏è‚É£  WITH-LOGBACK PROFILE - Maven-Only CI/CD Testing
        ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
        What:    Additional Maven profile for complete coverage
        Tests:   Logback converters and integration tests (~84 tests)
        Runtime: logback-classic (real Logback Logger)
        Exclude: slf4j-test-mock dependency
        Include: **/logback/**/*Test.java test classes only
        Include: src/logback-main/java (Logback converters - production code)
        Include: src/logback-test/java (Logback integration tests)

        IDE Support: ‚ùå No IDE support for running/debugging these tests

        Command: mvn clean test -P slf4j-2.0,with-logback
        Result:  1525 tests pass (1441 + 84)

        WHY THIS APPROACH?
        ==================
        ‚úÖ IDEs import the default configuration ‚Üí clean project structure
        ‚úÖ 99% of development work uses standard build ‚Üí no complexity
        ‚úÖ Logback tests verified in CI/CD ‚Üí complete coverage guaranteed
        ‚úÖ No SLF4J binding conflicts during development
        ‚úÖ No IDE confusion with multiple source roots
        ‚úÖ Developers can run/debug tests directly in IDE
        ‚úÖ Build matrix in CI/CD covers all combinations

        HOW IT WORKS (Technical Details):
        ==================================
        - Maven Surefire plugin has TWO executions:
          1. "default-test" (always active) ‚Üí runs core tests
          2. "logback-tests" (profile-activated) ‚Üí runs logback tests

        - Classpath isolation via <classpathDependencyExcludes>:
          * default-test: excludes logback-classic
          * logback-tests: excludes slf4j-test-mock

        - Source directories added conditionally:
          * with-logback profile uses build-helper-maven-plugin
          * Adds src/logback-main/java and src/logback-test/java
          * Only during Maven build, NOT imported by IDE

        ALTERNATIVE APPROACHES CONSIDERED (AND REJECTED):
        ==================================================
        ‚ùå Separate module (slf4j-toys-logback): Too much POM duplication
        ‚ùå Multiple IDE profiles: IDEs don't handle profile switching well
        ‚ùå JUnit tags: Cannot remove dependencies from classpath
        ‚ùå Conditional dependencies: Maven lacks runtime classpath isolation
        ‚ùå Both dependencies in classpath: ClassCastException at runtime

        IMPORTANT NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS:
        ================================
        üìå When working on logback converters (src/logback-main/java):
           - Edit files with any text editor or IDE (they're just not imported)
           - Build with Maven to compile and test: mvn test -P with-logback
           - Cannot run/debug these tests from IDE

        üìå When working on core features (Meter, Watcher, Reporter):
           - Full IDE support - run, debug, refactor as usual
           - No logback complexity - just pure SLF4J + MockLogger
           - This is 99% of development work

        üìå CI/CD Build Matrix:
           - Tests with slf4j-1.7 + javax.servlet (Java 8+)
           - Tests with slf4j-2.0 + javax.servlet (Java 11+)
           - Tests with slf4j-2.0 + jakarta.servlet (Java 11+)
           - All combinations run with and without logback profile

        For more details, see the inline comments in the <build> and <profiles> sections.

        Technical Decision Record:
        üìÑ doc/TDR-0031-ide-friendly-build-with-optional-logback-testing.md
        ================================================================================
    -->

